headline: Nvidia earnings, new home sales data, July PCE: What to Watch
summary: Asking for a Trend host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch next week, starting Monday, Aug. 25. More earnings reports will be out: PDD Holdings (PDD) on Monday, Okta (OKTA) on Tuesday, Nvidia (NVDA) and Abercrombie & Fitch (ANF) on Wednesday, Gap (GAP) and Dell (DELL) on Thursday, and more. New home sales data for July will be out on Monday morning, with economists expecting an increase to 630,000. July data for Personal Consumption Expenditures (PCE) — the Federal Reserve's preferred inflation gauge — will be published Friday morning. Economists expect numbers to hold relatively steady from June. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend.
